{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892426423,"sessionID":"ses_284912bd8ffepxCqbF5MehI1bN","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6fdb3a001RPSHuZS0irhsfI","messageID":"msg_d7b6fc438001ew8I6JWUXxoVlq","sessionID":"ses_284912bd8ffepxCqbF5MehI1bN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ### Component Diagram\n6: ```\n7: ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n8: Ōöé  CLI Interface  Ōöé\n9: Ōöé  (invoke.py)    Ōöé\n10: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n11:          Ōöé\n12: ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n13: Ōöé  CLI Interface  Ōöé\n14: Ōöé  (status.py)    Ōöé\n15: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n16:          Ōöé\n17: ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n18: ŌöéExecution Client Ōöé\n19: Ōöé(execution.py)   Ōöé\n20: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n21:          Ōöé\n22: ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n23: Ōöé Output FormatterŌöé\n24: Ōöé (formatter.py)  Ōöé\n25: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n26:          Ōöé HTTP\n27:     ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n28:     ŌöéBackend  Ōöé\n29:     Ōöé   API   Ōöé\n30:     ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ## Key Design Decisions\n34: \n35: ### Input Handling\n36: - Support multiple input formats: JSON string, key-value pairs, JSON file\n37: - Validate inputs against agent schema before submission\n38: - Merge multiple input sources (file + CLI args)\n39: \n40: ### Execution Modes\n41: - **Async mode (default)**: Submit and return execution ID immediately\n42: - **Sync mode**: Poll until completion or timeout\n43: \n44: ### Status Polling\n45: - Configurable polling interval\n46: - Exponential backoff for long-running executions\n47: - Exit immediately when execution completes or fails\n48: \n49: ### Output Formatting\n50: - JSON: Machine-readable, complete response data\n51: - Table: Human-readable, key status fields\n52: - Support for color-coded status indicators\n53: \n54: ### Error Handling\n55: - Clear error messages for common failure scenarios\n56: - Propagate backend error codes appropriately\n57: - Graceful handling of network issues\n58: \n59: ## Data Flow\n60: \n61: ### Invoke Command\n62: 1. Parse command arguments\n63: 2. Load and validate input parameters\n64: 3. Construct execution request payload\n65: 4. Submit to backend API\n66: 5. Handle response:\n67:    - Async: Display execution ID\n68:    - Sync: Poll status until completion\n69: 6. Format and display results\n70: \n71: ### Status Command\n72: 1. Parse command arguments\n73: 2. Validate execution ID format\n74: 3. Query backend for status\n75: 4. Format and display current state\n76: 5. If watch mode: repeat until terminal state\n77: \n78: ## API Integration\n79: \n80: ### Endpoints\n81: - `POST /api/v1/executions` - Submit new execution\n82: - `GET /api/v1/executions/{id}` - Query execution status\n83: - `GET /api/v1/executions/{id}/result` - Fetch execution results\n84: \n85: ### Response Handling\n86: - 2xx: Success, parse response body\n87: - 4xx: Client error, display helpful message\n88: - 5xx: Server error, suggest retry\n\n(End of file - total 88 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n```\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé  CLI Interface  Ōöé\nŌöé  (invoke.py)    Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n         Ōöé\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé  CLI Interface  Ōöé\nŌöé  (status.py)    Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n         Ōöé\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöéExecution Client Ōöé\nŌöé(execution.py)   Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775892426402,"end":1775892426422}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892426425,"sessionID":"ses_284912bd8ffepxCqbF5MehI1bN","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6fe03e001ILpO01JQuJ49X8","messageID":"msg_d7b6fc438001ew8I6JWUXxoVlq","sessionID":"ses_284912bd8ffepxCqbF5MehI1bN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Foundation\n4: \n5: ### Task 1.1: Execution Client Module\n6: **Objective**: Create the HTTP client for execution API communication\n7: \n8: **Steps**:\n9: 1. Create `cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`\n10: 2. Implement `ExecutionClient` class\n11: 3. Add methods for:\n12:    - `submit_execution(agent_id, inputs, options)`\n13:    - `get_status(execution_id)`\n14:    - `get_result(execution_id)`\n15: 4. Add error handling and retry logic\n16: 5. Write unit tests\n17: \n18: **Deliverables**:\n19: - `cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`\n20: - `tests/unit/test_execution_client.py`\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ### Task 1.2: Output Formatter Module\n25: **Objective**: Create output formatting utilities\n26: \n27: **Steps**:\n28: 1. Create `cmd/cli/internal/formatter.py`\n29: 2. Implement formatters for:\n30:    - JSON output\n31:    - Table output\n32:    - Status color coding\n33: 3. Add support for custom formatting options\n34: 4. Write unit tests\n35: \n36: **Deliverables**:\n37: - `cmd/cli/internal/formatter.py`\n38: - `tests/unit/test_formatter.py`\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Phase 2: Invoke Command\n43: \n44: ### Task 2.1: Input Parser\n45: **Objective**: Parse various input formats\n46: \n47: **Steps**:\n48: 1. Create input parsing utilities\n49: 2. Support JSON string, key-value pairs, file input\n50: 3. Validate input against basic schema\n51: 4. Write unit tests\n52: \n53: **Deliverables**:\n54: - `cmd/cli/internal/input_parser.py`\n55: - `tests/unit/test_input_parser.py`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Task 2.2: Invoke Command Implementation\n60: **Objective**: Implement the invoke command\n61: \n62: **Steps**:\n63: 1. Create `cmd/cli/invoke.py`\n64: 2. Implement argument parsing\n65: 3. Integrate with ExecutionClient\n66: 4. Implement sync and async modes\n67: 5. Add output formatting\n68: 6. Write unit tests\n69: \n70: **Deliverables**:\n71: - `cmd/cli/invoke.py`\n72: - `tests/unit/test_invoke_command.py`\n73: - `tests/integration/test_invoke_workflow.py`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Phase 3: Status Command\n78: \n79: ### Task 3.1: Status Command Implementation\n80: **Objective**: Implement the status command\n81: \n82: **Steps**:\n83: 1. Create `cmd/cli/status.py`\n84: 2. Implement argument parsing\n85: 3. Implement polling logic with configurable interval\n86: 4. Add watch mode support\n87: 5. Integrate with ExecutionClient\n88: 6. Write unit tests\n89: \n90: **Deliverables**:\n91: - `cmd/cli/status.py`\n92: - `tests/unit/test_status_command.py`\n93: - `tests/integration/test_status_workflow.py`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Phase 4: Integration\n98: \n99: ### Task 4.1: CLI Registration\n100: **Objective**: Register commands with main CLI\n101: \n102: **Steps**:\n103: 1. Update `cmd/cli/main.py`\n104: 2. Add invoke subcommand\n105: 3. Add status subcommand\n106: 4. Verify command hierarchy\n107: \n108: **Deliverables**:\n109: - Updated `cmd/cli/main.py`\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Task 4.2: End-to-End Testing\n114: **Objective**: Validate complete workflows\n115: \n116: **Steps**:\n117: 1. Create E2E test suite\n118: 2. Test invoke ŌåÆ status workflow\n119: 3. Test error scenarios\n120: 4. Test edge cases\n121: \n122: **Deliverables**:\n123: - `tests/e2e/test_invoke_status.py`\n124: - Test report\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## Phase 5: Documentation\n129: \n130: ### Task 5.1: Command Documentation\n131: **Objective**: Document usage and examples\n132: \n133: **Steps**:\n134: 1. Write invoke command documentation\n135: 2. Write status command documentation\n136: 3. Add examples to help text\n137: 4. Update README if needed\n138: \n139: **Deliverables**:\n140: - Updated documentation\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## Dependencies\n145: \n146: ### Prerequisites\n147: - AR-018 or later (CLI framework stable)\n148: - Backend execution API available\n149: \n150: ### Optional Enhancements\n151: - Real-time status updates via WebSocket (future)\n152: - Log streaming for running executions (future)\n153: \n154: ## Timeline\n155: \n156: | Phase | Tasks | Estimated Days |\n157: |-------|-------|----------------|\n158: | Phase 1 | 1.1, 1.2 | 1 |\n159: | Phase 2 | 2.1, 2.2 | 1.5 |\n160: | Phase 3 | 3.1 | 0.5 |\n161: | Phase 4 | 4.1, 4.2 | 0.5 |\n162: | Phase 5 | 5.1 | 0.5 |\n163: | **Total** | | **3** |\n\n(End of file - total 163 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż ŌĆö Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation\n\n### Task 1.1: Execution Client Module\n**Objective**: Create the HTTP client for execution API communication\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create `cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`\n2. Implement `ExecutionClient` class\n3. Add methods for:\n   - `submit_execution(agent_id, inputs, options)`\n   - `get_status(execution_id)`\n   - `get_result(execution_id)`\n4. Add error handling and retry logic\n5. Write unit tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_execution_client.py`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/plan.md","time":{"start":1775892426405,"end":1775892426423}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892426426,"sessionID":"ses_284912bd8ffepxCqbF5MehI1bN","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6fe53b001Gih7m3X9Vxws9I","messageID":"msg_d7b6fc438001ew8I6JWUXxoVlq","sessionID":"ses_284912bd8ffepxCqbF5MehI1bN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Invoke runtime for AgentCube CLI.\n2: \n3: This module provides the InvokeRuntime class for invoking agents.\n4: \"\"\"\n5: \n6: import logging\n7: from pathlib import Path\n8: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n9: \n10: from agentcube.utils.log import get_logger\n11: \n12: \n13: class InvokeRuntime:\n14:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n15: \n16:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n17:         \"\"\"Initialize InvokeRuntime.\n18: \n19:         Args:\n20:             verbose: Whether to enable verbose logging.\n21:             provider: The target provider ('agentcube' or 'k8s').\n22:         \"\"\"\n23:         self.verbose = verbose\n24:         self.provider = provider\n25:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n26: \n27:     def invoke(\n28:         self,\n29:         workspace_path: Path,\n30:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n31:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n32:     ) -> Any:\n33:         \"\"\"Invoke the agent.\n34: \n35:         Args:\n36:             workspace_path: Path to the agent workspace directory.\n37:             payload: The invocation payload.\n38:             headers: Optional HTTP headers.\n39: \n40:         Returns:\n41:             The invocation result.\n42:         \"\"\"\n43:         self.logger.info(\"Invoke operation not yet implemented\")\n44:         return {\"status\": \"not_implemented\"}\n\n(End of file - total 44 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Invoke runtime for AgentCube CLI.\n\nThis module provides the InvokeRuntime class for invoking agents.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.utils.log import get_logger\n\n\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize InvokeRuntime.\n\n        Args:\n            verbose: Whether to enable verbose logging.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py","time":{"start":1775892426407,"end":1775892426425}}}}
