ĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n              Ōöé                          Ōöé                        Ōöé\n              Ō¢╝                          Ō¢╝                        Ō¢╝\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé                           External APIs                                       Ōöé\nŌöé       Agent Metadata YAML         AgentRuntime CR           K8s API         Ōöé\nŌöé     (agent_metadata.yaml)    (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)  (Deployment)   Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n#### Invoke Command Flow\n```\n1. CLI parses arguments (workspace, payload, headers, provider)\n2. Validate payload is valid JSON\n3. Parse header strings into dict (format: \"key:value\")\n4. InvokeRuntime.invoke():\n   a. Load metadata from workspace\n   b. Validate prerequisites (agent_id for agentcube, endpoint for k8s)\n   c. Determine endpoint URL based on provider\n   d. Add session header if session_id exists in metadata\n   e. Send HTTP POST with payload\n   f. Return response\n5. CLI formats and displays result\n```\n\n#### Status Command Flow\n```\n1. CLI parses arguments (workspace, provider)\n2. StatusRuntime.get_status():\n   a. Load metadata from workspace\n   b. If no agent_id ŌåÆ return \"not_published\"\n   c. Based on provider:\n      - agentcube: Query AgentRuntime CR status\n      - k8s: Query Deployment/Service status\n   d. Return status dict\n3. CLI displays status in Rich Table\n4. Exit code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Module Structure\n\n### File Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke()` and `status()` commands (lines 379-430) |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` class for agent invocation |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` class for status checking |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for loading/saving metadata |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for CR operations |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for K8s resource operations |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```\ninvoke/status commands\n    Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ InvokeRuntime / StatusRuntime\n    Ōöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ MetadataService\n    Ōöé       Ōöé       ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ AgentMetadata (Pydantic model)\n    Ōöé       Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ AgentCubeProvider (if provider=agentcube)\n    Ōöé       Ōöé       ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Kubernetes client (custom resources)\n    Ōöé       ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ KubernetesProvider (if provider=k8s)\n    Ōöé               ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Kubernetes client (Deployment/Service)\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ httpx (for HTTP requests in invoke)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. CLI Commands (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n#### Invoke Command\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Implementation Logic:**\n\n```python\ndef invoke(...) -> None:\n    workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n    \n    # 1. Validate JSON payload\n    try:\n        payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        console.print(f\"Error: Invalid JSON payload - {e}\", style=\"red\")\n        raise typer.Exit(1)\n    \n    # 2. Parse headers\n    headers = {}\n    if header_list:\n        for header in header_list:\n            if \":\" not in header:\n                console.print(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\", style=\"red\")\n                raise typer.Exit(1)\n            key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n            headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    \n    # 3. Create runtime and invoke\n    runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n    \n    try:\n        with Progress(...) as progress:\n            task = progress.add_task(\"Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n            result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)\n            progress.update(task, completed=True)\n        \n        # 4. Display result\n        console.print(\"[green]Ō£ō[/green] Agent invoked successfully!\")\n        console.print_json(data=result)\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n```\n\n#### Status Command\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Implementation Logic:**\n\n```python\ndef status(...) -> None:\n    workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n    \n    runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n    \n    try:\n        status_result = runtime.get_status(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Display in Rich Table\n        table = Table(title=\"Agent Status\")\n        table.add_column(\"Property\", style=\"cyan\")\n        table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n        \n        for key, value in status_result.items():\n            table.add_row(key, str(value))\n        \n        console.print(table)\n        \n        # Exit with code 1 if not published or error\n        if status_result.get(\"status\") in (\"not_published\", \"error\"):\n            raise typer.Exit(1)\n            \n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"checking status\", verbose)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. InvokeRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n\n#### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the agent.\"\"\"\n        headers = headers or {}\n        \n        # Validate prerequisites and get metadata\n        metadata, endpoint, agent_id = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Add session header if available\n        if metadata.session_id:\n            headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n        \n        # Invoke based on provider\n        if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n            return self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path)\n        else:\n            return self._direct_http_invocation(endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path)\n```\n\n#### Key Methods\n\n**`_validate_invoke_prerequisites`**\n```python\ndef _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Validate that the agent can be invoked.\n    \n    Returns:\n        Tuple of (metadata, endpoint, agent_id)\n    \n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If metadata is missing required fields.\n    \"\"\"\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    \n    if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n        if not metadata.agent_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\")\n        if not metadata.router_url:\n            raise ValueError(\"router_url is required in metadata for agentcube provider\")\n        endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint or metadata.router_url\n        return metadata, endpoint, metadata.agent_id\n    else:\n        # k8s provider\n        if not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Kubernetes deployment found. Run 'publish --provider k8s' first.\")\n        endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint or self._build_k8s_endpoint(metadata)\n        return metadata, endpoint, metadata.agent_name\n```\n\n**`_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`**\n```python\nasync def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n    self,\n    agent_id: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    endpoint: str,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Invoke agent through AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR).\n    \n    For AgentRuntime CR deployments, rewrites URL to:\n    {base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n    \"\"\"\n    import httpx\n    \n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    \n    # Build invocation URL\n    if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n        namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n        agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n        base_url = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n        invoke_url = f\"{base_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n    else:\n        invoke_url = endpoint\n    \n    # Make request\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.post(\n            invoke_url,\n            json=payload,\n            headers=headers,\n            timeout=30.0,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n```\n\n**`_direct_http_invocation`**\n```python\nasync def _direct_http_invocation(\n    self,\n    endpoint: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    workspace_path: Path,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments.\"\"\"\n    import httpx\n    \n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.post(\n            endpoint,\n            json=payload,\n            headers=headers,\n            timeout=30.0,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. StatusRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n\n#### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for checking agent status.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n    \n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get the agent status.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Dict with keys:\n            - status: \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\", \"not_published\", etc.\n            - agent_name: The agent name\n            - agent_id: The agent ID (if published)\n            - endpoint: The agent endpoint (if available)\n            - provider: The provider used\n            - message: Human-readable status message\n        \"\"\"\n        provider = provider or self.provider\n        \n        try:\n            metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"error\",\n                \"message\": f\"No metadata found in {workspace_path}\",\n            }\n        \n        # Check if published\n        if not metadata.agent_id and not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"not_published\",\n                \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n                \"message\": \"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\",\n            }\n        \n        # Get status based on provider\n        if provider == \"agentcube\":\n            return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n        else:\n            return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n```\n\n#### Key Methods\n\n**`_get_k8s_status`**\n```python\ndef _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Get status for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n    from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n    \n    if not metadata.k8s_deployment:\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"error\",\n            \"message\": \"No Kubernetes deployment information found\",\n        }\n    \n    k8s = KubernetesProvider(\n        namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n        verbose=self.verbose,\n    )\n    \n    try:\n        agent_status = k8s.get_agent_status(metadata.k8s_deployment[\"name\"])\n        return {\n            \"status\": agent_status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n            \"endpoint\": metadata.agent_endpoint,\n            \"provider\": \"k8s\",\n            \"deployment\": metadata.k8s_deployment,\n            \"message\": f\"Deployment is {agent_status.get('status', 'unknown')}\",\n        }\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"error\",\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"message\": f\"Failed to get status: {e}\",\n        }\n```\n\n**`_get_cr_k8s_status`**\n```python\ndef _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Get status for AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n    from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n    \n    if not metadata.agent_id:\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"not_published\",\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"message\": \"Agent has not been published\",\n        }\n    \n    namespace = \"default\"\n    if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n        namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n    \n    provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n    \n    try:\n        cr = provider.get_agent_runtime(metadata.agent_name, namespace)\n        \n        if cr is None:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\",\n                \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n                \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n                \"message\": \"AgentRuntime CR not found in Kubernetes\",\n            }\n        \n        # Extract status from CR\n        cr_status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n        if cr_status:\n            status = cr_status.get(\"status\", \"created_no_status\")\n            endpoint = cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\") or metadata.agent_endpoint\n        else:\n            status = \"created_no_status\"\n            endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint\n        \n        return {\n            \"status\": status,\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n            \"endpoint\": endpoint,\n            \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n            \"message\": f\"AgentRuntime is {status}\",\n        }\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"error\",\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n            \"message\": f\"Failed to get status: {e}\",\n        }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Service Provider Integration\n\n#### AgentCubeProvider (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n\nThe `AgentCubeProvider` provides access to the AgentRuntime CR:\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR operations.\"\"\"\n    \n    CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n    CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n    \n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        \"\"\"Get an AgentRuntime CR by name.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The CR dict if found, None otherwise.\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            cr = self.custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.CR_GROUP,\n                version=self.CR_VERSION,\n                namespace=namespace,\n                plural=self.CR_PLURAL,\n                name=name,\n            )\n            return cr\n        except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                return None\n            raise\n```\n\n#### KubernetesProvider (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n\nThe `KubernetesProvider` provides access to standard K8s resources:\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service operations.\"\"\"\n    \n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get status of the agent deployment.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Dict with status info including:\n            - status: \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\"\n            - replicas: number of replicas\n            - available_replicas: number of available replicas\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(\n                name=self._sanitize_name(agent_name),\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n            )\n            \n            status = deployment.status\n            available = status.available_replicas or 0\n            desired = status.replicas or 0\n            \n            if available == desired and desired > 0:\n                state = \"ready\"\n            elif available < desired:\n                state = \"pending\"\n            else:\n                state = \"error\"\n            \n            return {\n                \"status\": state,\n                \"replicas\": desired,\n                \"available_replicas\": available,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            }\n            \n        except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                return {\"status\": \"not_found\"}\n            raise\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Models\n\n### AgentMetadata (Relevant Fields)\n\n| Field | Type | Used In |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | invoke, status |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | invoke, status (published check) |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (header) |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (endpoint) |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | invoke (endpoint fallback) |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict]` | status (provider selection) |\n\n### Status Response Schema\n\n```python\n{\n    \"status\": str,  # \"ready\", \"pending\", \"error\", \"not_published\", \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"created_no_status\"\n    \"agent_name\": str,\n    \"agent_id\": Optional[str],\n    \"endpoint\": Optional[str],\n    \"provider\": str,  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n    \"message\": str,\n    # For k8s provider:\n    \"deployment\": Optional[Dict[str, Any]],\n    # For agentcube provider:\n    # Additional CR status fields\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Patterns\n\nAll errors are handled via `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", style=\"red\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### Specific Error Cases\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n|----------|------------|---------|\n| Invalid JSON payload | `json.JSONDecodeError` | \"Invalid JSON payload - {details}\" |\n| Invalid header format | `typer.Exit(1)` | \"Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\" |\n| Agent not published | `ValueError` | \"Agent has not been published. Run 'publish' first.\" |\n| Missing router_url | `ValueError` | \"router_url is required in metadata for agentcube provider\" |\n| No K8s deployment | `ValueError` | \"No Kubernetes deployment found...\" |\n| HTTP error | `httpx.HTTPStatusError` | propagated with status code |\n| K8s API error | `kubernetes.client.ApiException` | propagated |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nThe invoke command respects these environment variables (via metadata):\n\n| Variable | Used For |\n|----------|----------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Default router URL if not in metadata |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload manager for AgentCube provider |\n\n### Metadata File Resolution\n\nThe `MetadataService` loads metadata in this order:\n1. `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n2. `{workspace}/agent.yaml` (fallback)\n3. `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **InvokeRuntime tests**:\n   - Payload validation\n   - Header parsing\n   - Endpoint URL construction\n   - Session header injection\n   - Error handling\n\n2. **StatusRuntime tests**:\n   - Status extraction from CR\n   - Status extraction from Deployment\n   - Not published detection\n   - Error state handling\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **Invoke command E2E**:\n   - Invoke with JSON payload\n   - Invoke with custom headers\n   - Invoke against both providers\n\n2. **Status command E2E**:\n   - Status for published agent\n   - Status for unpublished agent (exit code 1)\n   - Status for error state (exit code 1)\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Header handling**: Headers are parsed carefully to prevent injection attacks\n2. **No secrets in logs**: Verbose mode does not log sensitive headers\n3. **HTTPS preferred**: Endpoint URLs should use HTTPS in production\n4. **K8s RBAC**: Status checks require appropriate K8s permissions\n\n---\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **WebSocket support**: Real-time status updates\n2. **Log streaming**: Stream agent logs during invocation\n3. **Retry logic**: Automatic retry with exponential backoff\n4. **Batch invoke**: Invoke multiple agents in parallel\n5. **Output templating**: Custom output format templates\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n- [AgentCube Python SDK](../../python-sdk/design.md) - SDK design patterns\n- [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md) - CR API details\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/cli/main.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces